.:: Zebra puzzle ::.
There 5 different types of food: lemonberry, kale, grapes, garlic, lemon
There are 5 different nationalities: english, spanish, ukranian, norwegian, japanese
The people use 5 different means of transport: roller, bus, car, subway, trike
There are 5 different favourite beverages: coffee, tea, milk, orange-juice, water
The people's birthday is in 5 different months: august, april, september, november, january

1. the english is the person eating lemonberry
2. the spanish is the person who's birthday is in august
3. the person drinking coffee is the person eating kale
4. the ukranian is the person drinking tea
5. the person eating kale is to the right of the person eating grapes
6. the person driving the roller is the person who's birthday is in january
7. the person driving the bus is the person eating garlic
8. the person drinking milk is in the middle
9. the norwegian is on the far left
10. the person driving the car is on the left or right of the person who's birthday is in april
11. the person driving the bus is to the left or right of the person who's birthday is in november
12. the person driving the subway is the person drinking orange-juice
13. the japanese is the person driving the trike
14. the norwegian is to the left or right of the person eating lemon

.:: Answer ::.
